The US amends the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must present themselves before they talk at the consulate to the service departments for visa applications; costs will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa will be changed in the US Embassy and in the consulates.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) prior to their consultation with the Consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be reviewed by the Consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirations, including:
The total cost of processing the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the equivalent of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who just want to extend their visas don't have to talk in the consulate, they only have to imagine themselves at the next ASC, where they present their documents and their fingerprints.
As the biometric data are collected in the ASC, applicants who need a second appointment for the consulate will remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Chihuahua, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer have to pay the service charge of 26 dollars.
Further information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/bolets/sp101201_Visas-FAQ.html
